<%- include('partials/header') %>

<div class="support-page">
  <div class="support-hero">
    <h1 data-i18n="support.title">üÜò Support & Resources</h1>
    <p data-i18n="support.subtitle">Need help? Find all the resources you need to get started or resolve issues.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="support-grid">
    <!-- GitHub -->
    <a href="https://github.com/Heliox1119/Werewolf-bot" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="support-card support-card-github" id="github">
      <span class="support-card-icon">üíª</span>
      <h3>GitHub</h3>
      <p data-i18n="support.github_desc">View the source code, report bugs, request features, and contribute to the project.</p>
      <span class="btn btn-sm btn-outline" data-i18n="support.github_btn">View Repository ‚Üí</span>
    </a>

    <!-- Discord -->
    <a href="#" class="support-card support-card-discord" id="discord">
      <span class="support-card-icon">üí¨</span>
      <h3>Discord</h3>
      <p data-i18n="support.discord_desc">Join our community server for live help, announcements, and discussion with other players.</p>
      <span class="btn btn-sm btn-discord" data-i18n="support.discord_btn">Join Server ‚Üí</span>
    </a>

    <!-- Documentation -->
    <a href="/docs" class="support-card support-card-docs">
      <span class="support-card-icon">üìö</span>
      <h3 data-i18n="support.docs_title">Documentation</h3>
      <p data-i18n="support.docs_desc">Complete wiki with all roles, commands, mechanics and configuration options explained in detail.</p>
      <span class="btn btn-sm btn-primary" data-i18n="support.docs_btn">Read the Wiki ‚Üí</span>
    </a>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <div class="support-faq" id="faq">
    <h2>‚ùì <span data-i18n="support.faq_title">Frequently Asked Questions</span></h2>

    <div class="doc-collapsible">
      <div class="doc-collapsible-header" data-toggle="faq-1">
        <span data-i18n="support.faq_q1">How do I invite the bot to my server?</span>
        <span class="doc-collapsible-arrow">‚ñ∏</span>
      </div>
      <div class="doc-collapsible-body">
        <p data-i18n="support.faq_a1">Use the invite link from the GitHub repository or the bot's profile. The bot needs Administrator permissions to manage channels, roles, and voice muting.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-collapsible">
      <div class="doc-collapsible-header" data-toggle="faq-2">
        <span data-i18n="support.faq_q2">What is the minimum number of players?</span>
        <span class="doc-collapsible-arrow">‚ñ∏</span>
      </div>
      <div class="doc-collapsible-body">
        <p data-i18n="support.faq_a2">You need at least 4 players to start a game. For the best experience with all roles, 8-12 players is recommended.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-collapsible">
      <div class="doc-collapsible-header" data-toggle="faq-3">
        <span data-i18n="support.faq_q3">How do I change the language?</span>
        <span class="doc-collapsible-arrow">‚ñ∏</span>
      </div>
      <div class="doc-collapsible-body">
        <p data-i18n="support.faq_a3">Use the /lang command followed by "fr" for French or "en" for English. This changes the bot's language for the entire server.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-collapsible">
      <div class="doc-collapsible-header" data-toggle="faq-4">
        <span data-i18n="support.faq_q4">Can I customize which roles are in the game?</span>
        <span class="doc-collapsible-arrow">‚ñ∏</span>
      </div>
      <div class="doc-collapsible-body">
        <p data-i18n="support.faq_a4">Yes! Use /setrules to enable or disable specific roles, change wolf count, and configure other game options per server.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-collapsible">
      <div class="doc-collapsible-header" data-toggle="faq-5">
        <span data-i18n="support.faq_q5">Why are my players not being muted/unmuted?</span>
        <span class="doc-collapsible-arrow">‚ñ∏</span>
      </div>
      <div class="doc-collapsible-body">
        <p data-i18n="support.faq_a5">Make sure the bot has the "Mute Members" permission. Players also need to be connected to the game's voice channel for voice management to work.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-collapsible">
      <div class="doc-collapsible-header" data-toggle="faq-6">
        <span data-i18n="support.faq_q6">The game is stuck, what do I do?</span>
        <span class="doc-collapsible-arrow">‚ñ∏</span>
      </div>
      <div class="doc-collapsible-body">
        <p data-i18n="support.faq_a6">An admin can use /nextphase to force advance to the next phase, or /force-end to immediately end the game. Use /clear to clean up channels.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-collapsible">
      <div class="doc-collapsible-header" data-toggle="faq-7">
        <span data-i18n="support.faq_q7">How does the ELO system work?</span>
        <span class="doc-collapsible-arrow">‚ñ∏</span>
      </div>
      <div class="doc-collapsible-body">
        <p data-i18n="support.faq_a7">Every player starts at 1000 ELO. Winning increases your rating and losing decreases it. Your tier (Iron ‚Üí Alpha Wolf) is determined by your ELO range. Use /stats to check your current rating.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  // FAQ collapsible toggle via event delegation
  document.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
    var header = e.target.closest('.doc-collapsible-header');
    if (!header) return;
    var collapsible = header.parentElement;
    if (collapsible) collapsible.classList.toggle('open');
  });
</script>

